caption: Yummy drinks and really nice staff! The interior is also super nice and cozy!
Had the Honeydew Melon smoothie with Tahitian Vanilla ice cream..  Really like all the jelly like goodies inside as well as the subtle natural fruit flavor.  Very understated,high quality beverage.
Awesome place! The staff was great and the drinks are literally amazing. I got the mango smoothie with cheese foam and it was so good! Also the pancakes are out of this world.
Seating area was closed, service was perfect! Love the tea options and must try the clear/crystal boba. Was still sweet at 50% sweetness, tea was nice!

(Translated by Google) I ordered mango mojito (sugar content: 50%) and brown sugar tapioca milk (sugar content: 75%). I saw a review saying that the sugar content is not too sweet, so I tried to order with reference to it, but it was moderately sweet.  I added konjac to the mango mojito, but it matched the refreshing mojito and was very delicious! The brown sugar tapioca milk was a little lukewarm because it puts warm tapioca in it, but it was mochi mochi because it was warm tapioca! (If you can make a lot of ice, it will be delicious)  The clerk who received the order was very kind 👍🏻 There was also a Japanese menu. When we went, it was on the table in front of the cash register.  I couldn't drink it in the store, but the interior was very fashionable and cute 🕊  If you are looking for a drinker near here, please go here!  (Original) マンゴーモヒート(糖度:50%)と黒糖タピオカミルク(糖度:75%)を頼みました。糖度は、甘すぎないと言うレビューを見ましたので、それを参考にして注文してみましたが、適度な甘さでした。  マンゴーモヒートにはこんにゃくを追加で入れてみましたが、爽やかなモヒートとマッチしてとっても美味しかったです！ 黒糖タピオカミルクは、温かいタピオカを入れてくれるので、少しぬるかったですが、温かいタピオカなのでモッチモチでした！(氷多めとかにできるなら、美味しくなると思います)  注文を受けてくれた店員さんがとても親切でした👍🏻 日本語のメニューもありました。私たちが行った時は、レジの前の台に置いてありました。  店内で飲むことはできませんでしたが、内装がとてもおしゃれで可愛かったです🕊  もし、ここの近くで何か飲み者を探しているなら、ぜひここに行ってみてください！
Cute staff
I love the Mango drink
Delicious fruit teas - so refreshing and unique flavors. They use real fruit,  not concentrate, which makes all the difference. The staff was really nice too. Highly recommend

Great service and teas.  I especially love their avocado smoothie because they infuse it with green tea to alleviate the heaviness w just avocado.  So it leaves you with a very refreshing after taste instead of heavy creaminess.  Their Souffle pancakes are great too and they are now doing a promo where you get a drink and pancakes for $12.50 until 12/15!
Nice ambiance. Tried their soufflé pancakes & they're delicious. A bit pricey but it's worth it. Also had da strawberry milk with boba. It's refreshing & boba was soft & chewy.
We ordered the smoothies which were simply delicious.  There was a steady stream of customers, and the staff was cheerful and efficient.  We're going back for the soufflés and gelato!

My new go-to drinks: watermelon smoothie and honeydew smoothie. Surprisingly refreshing and beyond my expectations as I usually picky about smoothies. I love how they only use fresh fruits without powders. Plus the bright and modern seating area, I would want to sit here on my butt all day lol

My favorite one is the brown sugar boba tea.  Smooth, silky and a perfect combination of richness and freshness.  Took my co-workers to there and everyone loved it.  One of our missions during the pandemic is to try all flavors on their menu.

Discovered this nicely designed tea shop when we were out looking for lunch options.  Love the contemporary design.  I wish we could sit there chill and sip our tea ( Hopefully,  when covid is over).  What I like most is the option for sweetness of tea.  I usually avoid too much sugar intake.  25% sweetness is perfect for me.  You can also ask for less ice, so your drink isn’t so diluted.  All in all,  they customize your drinks to your liking. Love it!
Highly recommended.

Thanks to Covid... I haven’t been able to dine in at this elegant boba tea cafe to enjoy my milk tea and soufflé pancakes yet. My favorite drinks so far are jasmine milk tea, mango Smoogurt and classic milk tea (25% sweet) with brown sugar boba and cheese foam. They offer free 1hr parking at Salt or behind Hmart, and you can order online in advance for takeout. I love their soufflé pancakes but it takes 20mins waiting time because it’s made to order! So order in advance!!

Delicious smoothies!!! Friendly staff and beautiful setup!!! I wish I get to sit inside and do my work in a sunny afternoon... let’s hope we all get to do it soon enough. I had a cheese foam topped peachy smoothie which is super refreshing and creamy too adding the cheesy top. However, if you are not a fun of the sweet and savory contrast in your smoothie, try their milk tea instead - my mom didn’t care much for the cheesy top, but she would definitely go again for the traditional milk tea. It’s well balanced with the sweetness of the milk and fragrance of the tea - just like the one you would taste in Hong Kong, but in a much more refined version. Price wise... it’s on the pricier end, but being at Kakaako, decorated with the most modern and beautiful decor (they prob had an interior designer do it professionally), using very good quality and stylish material for the drinks, I say they price like any smart business person would. A plus, the photo opportunity... haha any drink you order it’s an art. Adding the backdrop of their cute little shop - what else do you ask for when you enjoy the drink while having hundreds (if not thousands) of your friends envy you at the same time?!! Love love love this place. I’d go every chance I have when I’m in the area. Oh, btw, they validate a hour of parking too when you park at Hmart next door.
A modern and nice milk tea place, located in Kakaako, near by H Mart. I love their fruit tea, it tastes awesome. Looking forward to dine in with friends.

I went in to order the peach smoothie and it does not taste good. On top of that they left the scan tags while they make the smoothie. I immediately trash my drink after that. Please at least peel off the tag before cutting it. This made me wonder if they even wash the fruits before they use it. I will never come back again.

After I been here my first time, I don’t want to come here the second time. All the products  are really really expensive and you could taste that the fruits are also not fresh. After I drank it I felt uncomfortable the whole day.

(Translated by Google) 2020.9.26 visit I couldn't eat or drink in the store on that day, so it was only takeout. I ordered strawberry milk. You can choose the sweetness. It seems to be modest in sweetness for Hawaii, I chose 75% sweetness and it was just right 😊  (Original) 2020.9.26来店 この日はまだ店内飲食はできず、テイクアウトオンリーでした。ストロベリーミルクをオーダー。甘さは選べます。ハワイにしては甘さ控えめなようで、私は甘さ75%を選んで、ちょうど良かったです😊

Very lovely cafe with beautiful modern decor. I would love to stay here to read a book or to work on something but unfortunately no dine-in service provided currently. There’re a few benches outside. Foods and drinks were delicious just a little on the pricey side but well it’s located at the heart of Kakaako so that’s kinda expected.

First of all I would say the interior of the shop looks very nice. It is located in a convince location in kakaako with easy street parkings around. My girlfriend and I went to the shop on a Tuesday afternoon. When we first enter the shop it seems very fresh and clean since they recently opened. Me and my girlfriend were so excited to try this place out since we heard so much good things about it but the result was such a disappointed. I know this may not seem important to other people but during this pandemic time cleanliness are something we should pay close attention to. When we were waiting in line we notice some customers in front paid cash for their drink. Then the cashier received the she cash went straight to help making drinks without washing or sanitizing her hands. This should of been the first sign that we should of leave. The ordering process was smooth and we got our drink reletively quick. The drinks were comparatively expensive not sure if it is because of their location.  We ordered two drinks and it cost about 20 dollars that's crazy!!!  The drinks looks nice however let me tell you it definitely not worth the price. With the fruit oolong tea I can taste that they use fruit Jam and mixed with water. For the mango smoogurt too it taste like mango juice not fresh mango that they claim. Both drinks were a total disappointment. The value of the drinks does not match with the price. This may probably be the only time we will be coming to this place. Please do not use fruit juice or jams and advertise as " fresh fruit". If you are by the area don't care about the taste and have a lot of cash in hand please do try this place out.
nice staff really good smoothies and i cant wait to suffer through all my college homework here when this place opens up

Delicious teas and smoothies, friendly staff, the only thing you could ask for is to sit down inside; which understandably isn't happening. Ordered the watermelon smoothie (refreshing), blueberry & strawberry smoothie (savory cheese foam? yummy), and a jasmine milk tea w/ boba (boba has a good texture and the tea matches it well) as they were out of their regular milk tea and all are great (partner got into his early lol)
You can only get drinks right now but its fine. Smoothies are really tasty and delicious.  Its new at this location so if your into bobba give it a go.
Milk tea and souffle pancake were awesome!
